id: pm-dw5s
title: Extend pm validate with low-signal metadata quality checks
description: Add explicit validate diagnostics for placeholder-style metadata so governance quality regressions are detected before large cleanup sweeps are required.
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[4]: governance,metadata,pm-cli,validation
created_at: "2026-04-04T21:55:14.472Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-05T21:44:33.714Z"
deadline: "2026-04-18T21:55:14.472Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "pm validate can detect configured low-signal metadata patterns, report affected item IDs with rule names, and optionally fail CI gates when quality thresholds are exceeded."
definition_of_ready: Placeholder pattern catalog and expected diagnostic format are agreed with maintainers.
goal: Governance operations by default
objective: Prevent placeholder metadata regressions
value: Shifts metadata quality from reactive cleanup to proactive validation
impact: Reduces future governance drift and manual audit effort
outcome: Low-signal metadata is surfaced automatically during validation
why_now: This sweep identified hundreds of placeholder fields that were not visible in current validate checks.
parent: pm-5rjn
reviewer: maintainer-review
risk: medium
confidence: medium
sprint: governance-followups
release: vnext
reporter: codex-agent
severity: medium
environment: linux
repro_steps: Run pm validate on a tracker containing placeholder metadata and observe that current checks do not flag low-signal fields.
affected_version: 2026.3.12
component: validate-metadata-quality
regression: false
customer_impact: Teams gain earlier detection of tracker quality drift and lower remediation cost.
comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:14.472Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm search 'validate placeholder metadata blocked_reason unblock_note repro_steps' --limit 20; pm search 'External audit follow-up: validation and large-output ergonomics' --limit 20; pm list-open --limit 20. Net-new because existing validation items focus on structural checks,not semantic low-signal metadata detection."
  "2026-04-05T03:08:05.985Z",codex-agent,"Scope extension for external issue #4: add default-on remediation command templates for missing resolution metadata in pm validate output details."
  "2026-04-05T03:26:56.486Z",codex-agent,"Progress: added default-on resolution remediation hints in validate output details. Resolution check now emits deterministic pm update <id> command templates for missing resolution/expected_result/actual_result fields (additive detail fields only, warning tokens unchanged), so both TOON and JSON outputs include actionable remediation by default. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts passed."
  "2026-04-05T03:46:59.542Z",codex-agent,Added default remediation command templates for missing resolution fields in validate outputs; smoke checked validate --check-resolution --json emits missing_resolution_remediation_hints with pm update templates.
  "2026-04-05T20:39:53.229Z",codex-agent,Duplicate-check evidence refreshed; reusing canonical validate metadata lineage for strict profile/configurable required-field expansion (no duplicate item created).
  "2026-04-05T21:00:37.808Z",codex-agent,"Progress: added validate metadata profiles (core|strict|custom), settings-backed custom required-field policy, --metadata-profile CLI override, and new config keys metadata-validation-profile + metadata-required-fields with list/get/export/set support. Added completion/contracts/Pi wrapper parity and targeted unit/integration coverage. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/unit/config-command.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts passed."
  "2026-04-05T21:44:33.714Z",codex-agent,"Regression follow-up: updated settings-store deterministic serialization expectation to include validation.metadata_profile and validation.metadata_required_fields so full-suite verification aligns with metadata-profile settings expansion."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:14.472Z",codex-agent,Checks should be configurable and avoid false positives by supporting per-rule opt-outs and rule versioning.
